menu "SPI NAND Flash configuration"

    config NAND_FLASH_VERIFY_WRITE
        bool "Verify SPI NAND flash writes"
        default n
        help
            If this option is enabled, any time SPI NAND flash is written then the data will be read
            back and verified. This can catch hardware problems with SPI NAND flash, or flash which
            was not erased before verification.

    config NAND_FLASH_ENABLE_BDL
        bool "Enable Block Device Layer (BDL) support"
        default n
        help
            Enable Block Device Layer (BDL) support for SPI NAND Flash. This provides:
            - Standard esp_blockdev_t interface for layered architecture
            - Flash Block Device Layer (raw NAND flash access)
            - Wear-Leveling Block Device Layer (logical sector access with wear leveling)
            - Advanced layered API (spi_nand_flash_init_with_layers)
            When disabled, only the legacy API is available.

            Note: This option requires ESP-IDF >= 6.0 (esp_blockdev component).
            Enabling this on ESP-IDF < 6.0 will result in a build error.

    config NAND_ENABLE_STATS
        bool "Host test statistics enabled"
        depends on IDF_TARGET_LINUX
        default n
        help
            This option enables gathering host test statistics and SPI NAND flash wear levelling simulation.

    menu "Generic chip detection (fallback when chip not in database and not ONFI supported)"

        config SPI_NAND_GENERIC_MANUAL
            bool "Enable manual configuration fallback"
            default n
            help
                When the chip is not in the driver database and ONFI parameter page detection fails,
                allow initializing the chip using manual geometry and timing from the options below.
                Use only for development or when the chip datasheet is known.

        config SPI_NAND_GENERIC_PAGE_SIZE
            int "Manual: page size in bytes"
            depends on SPI_NAND_GENERIC_MANUAL
            default 2048
            range 512 8192
            help
                Page size (data area) from chip datasheet. Must be a power of 2 (e.g. 2048, 4096).

        config SPI_NAND_GENERIC_PAGES_PER_BLOCK
            int "Manual: pages per block"
            depends on SPI_NAND_GENERIC_MANUAL
            default 64
            range 32 256
            help
                Number of pages per block from chip datasheet. Must be a power of 2 (e.g. 64, 128).

        config SPI_NAND_GENERIC_BLOCKS
            int "Manual: number of blocks"
            depends on SPI_NAND_GENERIC_MANUAL
            default 1024
            range 256 8192
            help
                Total number of blocks from chip datasheet (e.g. 1024, 2048, 4096).

        config SPI_NAND_GENERIC_T_R_US
            int "Manual: page read time (us)"
            depends on SPI_NAND_GENERIC_MANUAL
            default 250
            range 1 1000
            help
                Typical/maximum page read time in microseconds (t_R from datasheet).

        config SPI_NAND_GENERIC_T_PROG_US
            int "Manual: page program time (us)"
            depends on SPI_NAND_GENERIC_MANUAL
            default 500
            range 1 10000
            help
                Typical/maximum page program time in microseconds (t_PROG from datasheet).

        config SPI_NAND_GENERIC_T_BERS_US
            int "Manual: block erase time (us)"
            depends on SPI_NAND_GENERIC_MANUAL
            default 3500
            range 100 50000
            help
                Typical/maximum block erase time in microseconds (t_BERS from datasheet).

    endmenu

endmenu
